data.description:
You have a database emulation
((a class with some Lists (database tables)).

You don't know the names of the Lists and their number.

All Lists are public {get;} properties

the result should be output only from those Lists in which the Generic Type Argument implements the ISearchable interface

Write a method that takes a database(IDatabaseEmulation)
and a string (what is being searched in the database tables)
and returns a List<SearchModel>



The search must ignore the case

the search should only check whether the search query is contained in the Name, and not compare the strings completely


```C#
public interface IDataBaseEmulation
{
    //Some Lists in implementations
}
public interface ISearchable
{
    string Name { get; set; }
}
public class SearchModel
{
    public string Name { get; set; }
    public string TableName { get; set; }
}
```
